# Claude Instructions

## Local Development

Start local server from project root:
```bash
cd /Users/jupiter/Projects/rent-vibe-stack-sync && python3 -m http.server 8080
```

Then visit:
- Hub: http://localhost:8080/
- Rent Vibes: http://localhost:8080/rent-vibes/
- Landlord Login: http://localhost:8080/landlord-login/

## Project Structure

- `/index.html` - Hub homepage (project cards)
- `/css/styles.css` - Shared styles for all pages
- `/rent-vibes/` - All RentVibes prototype files
- `/landlord-login/` - Landlord Login placeholder
- `/docs/` - Sprint/milestone documentation
- `/docs/old/` - Archived files (gitignored)

## Deployment

GitHub is connected to Vercel - pushing to main auto-deploys:
```bash
git push origin main
```

Fallback (manual deploy if needed):
```bash
npx vercel --prod --yes
```

Live: https://rent-vibe-stack-sync.vercel.app/

## Notes

- Static HTML/CSS/JS site (no build step)
- CSS is shared at root level (`/css/styles.css`)
- Wait for user to verify locally before pushing to GitHub
